 *
 * PROBLEM
 * -------
 * Phase 2 Payment Flow needs durable persistence for partial charges
 * (e.g. customer pays return shipping, repair-out-of-warranty fee, extra
 * parts) against a `claim_ticket` CPT. Bank info MUST be snapshotted at
 * INSERT time so admin's mid-flow bank-account edits do not invalidate
 * customer's already-issued Flex card (see §6.4 immutability contract).
 *
 * SOLUTION
 * --------
 * Single canonical table `wp_dinoco_claim_charges` (mirrors Idempotency
 * Helper / Flag Audit Log lazy-install pattern) with:
 *   - 7-column bank snapshot (bank_code/account/holder/name/branch/context)
 *   - Slip2Go verify cache (slip_image_url / slip_ref_hash / slip_verify_data)
 *   - State machine column (status VARCHAR(24))
 *   - 4 KEY indexes for hot-path lookups
 *   - 1 UNIQUE constraint (slip_ref_hash) preventing slip replay
 *   - Optional CHECK constraints on MySQL 8.0.16+ (PHP validator is primary
 *     defense — see B2F V.7.0 / Phase 4 migration pattern)
 *   - 90-day retention cron for cancelled/expired rows
 *
 * DESIGN PRINCIPLES
 *   - LAZY INSTALL  — schema version flag on admin_init (autoload=false)
 *   - IDEMPOTENT    — re-runs are safe (INFORMATION_SCHEMA gated ALTERs)
 *   - ADDITIVE      — zero behaviour change at existing endpoints
 *                     (this file builds NOTHING but schema + table-name
 *                     helper + retention cron)
 *   - NON-THROWING  — best-effort everywhere; failures fall through
 *
 * Public API:
 *   dinoco_claim_charges_table_name() : string  (returns prefixed table)
 *   dinoco_claim_charges_schema_install() : void  (idempotent install)
 *   dinoco_claim_charges_cleanup_run() : int  (cron + manual)
 *   DINOCO_CLAIM_CHARGES_SCHEMA_VERSION (const) — current schema version
 *   DINOCO_CLAIM_CHARGES_REASON_WHITELIST (const) — 4 canonical reason values
 *   DINOCO_CLAIM_CHARGES_STATUS_WHITELIST (const) — 7 canonical status values
 *   DINOCO_CLAIM_CHARGES_BANK_CONTEXT_WHITELIST (const) — 2 context values
 *
 * NOT included in this snippet (defer to later Phase 2 tasks):
 *   - Charge create/read/update/refund REST handlers (Phase 2.2 — [#1212])
 *   - Service Center "Charges" admin section (Phase 2.4 — Snippet [#27])
 *   - Customer LIFF UI (Phase 2.5)
 *   - Slip2Go verify wrapper `dinoco_verify_slip_for_claim` (Phase 2.2 B1)
 *   - Expiry cron `dinoco_claim_charge_expire_cron` (Phase 2.6)
 *
 * Spec reference:
 *   docs/feature-specs/FEATURE-SPEC-CLAIM-LIFECYCLE-2026-05-13.md
 *   §3.1 (DDL) + §6.4 (immutability contract) + Phase 2 Task 2.1 (7h budget)
 *
 * Related snippets (cross-refs use [#NNNN] format to avoid drift detector
 * false-positive — actual DB_IDs):
